Package etomica.util.collections

Class IndexMap<V>

  • java.lang.Object
    • etomica.util.collections.IndexMap<V>
  • Type Parameters:
    V - the type of value contained in this map.
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.util.Map<java.lang.Integer,V>

    public final class IndexMap<V>
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.util.Map<java.lang.Integer,V>
    An specialized implementation of Map which is designed for mapping an index to a value. It is backed by an array but allows inserting out of index order without having to manage array resizing manually.

    This should not be used as a general int-keyed map as the backing array will take space up to the largest key. Use this when you have an expected maximum index (but not necessarily known or constant) that you need to sporadically fill mappings up to.

      • IndexMap

        public IndexMap​(int initialCapacity,
                int reservoirSize)
        Creates a new map with the given initial capacity and reservoir size. The backing array will be of size initialCapacity + reservoirSize, and keys up to that value can be added without the array being resized.
        Parameters:
        initialCapacity - the base capacity to start with.
        reservoirSize - the amount of padding to be included in the backing array.
